<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFE6823459A317CBE6DFB38" blockId="11.[151,1437,711,1206]" pageId="11" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFE6823459A317CBB40FB1C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1143,1169]" pageId="11" pageNumber="294">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFFE682344193173BB88FB1C" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="1990" box="[324,499,1143,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blythi">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFE682344193173BB88FB1C" box="[324,499,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="294">Ecnomus blythi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded from many sites in the NT and five sites in northern WA (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFFE682345C23190BB26FB38" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[159,349,1179,1205]" pageId="11" pageNumber="294" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref14543" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (1990) The Australian species of Ecnomus McLachlan (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 51, 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j / mmv. 1990.51.01" type="journal article" year="1990">Cartwright 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Many males are recorded from a further seven NT localities.
</paragraph>
